Some shortcuts of Visual Studio Code:

To open the terminal: ctrl + J

To open a file: ctrl + O

To save a file: ctrl + S

To open command palette: ctrl + shift + P

To open settings: ctrl + ,

To cut line: ctrl + X

To copy selection: ctrl + C

To paste into terminal: ctrl + V

To select current line: ctrl + L

To put cursors on multiple lines: ctrl + alt

To select until the end of the word: shift + alt + â†’ (right arrow)

To select all results: alt + enter

To trim white spaces: ctrl + K + X

To Goto line: ctrl + G

To run the code: F5

To find: ctrl + F

To replace: ctrl + H

To close Window: ctrl + shift + W
